st kind of bosonic topological orders\nthat have no non-trivial topological excitations. We find that this kind of\ntopological orders form a $\\mathbb{Z}$ class in 2+1D (with gapless edge), a\n$\\mathbb{Z}_2$ class in 4+1D (with gappable boundary), and a $\\mathbb{Z}\\oplus\n\\mathbb{Z}$ class in 6+1D (with gapless boundary).\n","versions":[{"version":"v1","created":"Thu, 22 May 2014 18:54:09 GMT"}],"update_date":"2014-05-23"}
